Your reference isn&#39;t a reference. It&#39;s a copy. You need to do this:

    auto&amp; reference = locations[item-&gt;x][item-&gt;y][item-&gt;z];
    //  ^

C++ is value-semantics-by-default, you have to opt-in to taking a reference.

It seems you forgot parentheses in this expression

    auto reference = locations[item-&gt;x()][item-&gt;y()][item-&gt;z()];
                                      ^^         ^^         ^^

or such a stetament

    locations[item-&gt;x()][item-&gt;y()][item-&gt;z()].back()-&gt;LocationIndexHandler::set_index(item-&gt;LocationIndexHandler::index()); 

shall be written without the parentheses.

In any case you can also to use the following approach to define a reference

    decltype( auto ) reference = ( locations[item-&gt;x()][item-&gt;y()][item-&gt;z()] );

